content.problemStatement:
The `replace(CharSequence target, CharSequence replacement)` method in Java is used to replace **all occurrences of a specified substring** (sequence of characters) with another substring. Unlike the `replace(char, char)` method, this version allows replacing entire words or phrases instead of single characters.

**Syntax:**

```java
String newString = originalString.replace("target", "replacement");
```

---

**Example:**

```java
class Seedit {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Declare and initialize a string
        String sentence = "I love Python programming";

        // Replace "Python" with "Java"
        String modifiedSentence = sentence.replace("Python", "Java");

        // Print the result
        System.out.println("Modified Sentence: " + modifiedSentence);
    }
}
```

**Expected Output:**

```default
Modified Sentence: I love Java programming
```

